Stock Market Analysis and Sentiment Tool

Overview
This tool is designed to analyze the stock market by fetching historical data, analyzing sentiment from news headlines, and performing various data operations. It also includes a Flask-based web server to interactively display analysis results through a web interface.

Features
Stock Data Retrieval: Leverage yfinance to download historical stock data.
News Sentiment Analysis: Use requests and TextBlob to fetch and analyze sentiments from news headlines relevant to specified stock tickers.
Database Management: Utilize SQLAlchemy to manage operations on a SQLite database, storing and retrieving stock and sentiment data efficiently.
Data Visualization: Generate plots for stock trends and moving averages using matplotlib.
Stock Price Prediction: Implement predictive analytics using a linear regression model trained on historical data.
Interactive API: Offer a Flask-based web API for data fetching and visualization.
Installation
Before installing, ensure you have Python installed on your system. Then, follow these steps:

Install Dependencies:
bash
Copy code
pip install flask sqlalchemy yfinance requests textblob numpy pandas matplotlib
Clone the Repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/44Jacob/FinDataTechAnalysis-.git
Run the Application:
Navigate to the project directory and execute:
bash
Copy code
python app.py
Usage
Once the server is running, you can access the API endpoints to interact with the system:

Load Data: GET /api/v1.0/load_data/<tickers> (Replace <tickers> with a list of stock tickers to fetch and analyze).
Fetch Processed Data: GET /api/v1.0/stock_data (Retrieves and displays average sentiment scores and other analysis results).

